# Roger Studio — root .env.example
#
# Most configuration lives in backend/.env.example (LLM providers,
# HuggingFace tokens, OlmoEarth runtime). The frontend Vite build
# currently reads ZERO env vars (no VITE_* usage in the codebase —
# the old VITE_CESIUM_ION_TOKEN reference was dropped when CesiumJS
# was switched to public default tilesets).
#
# Keep this file as the top-level pointer so new contributors don't
# miss backend/.env.example. If/when the frontend grows real env
# vars, declare them here with the VITE_ prefix.


# -- pointer --

# Backend runtime configuration:
#   see ./backend/.env.example  (LLM runtime, HF token, 4 cloud chat
#                                providers, OlmoEarth inference knobs)


# -- reserved slots (no code reads these today; left as the documented
#    place to put credentials if we wire the corresponding data source) --

# Copernicus Data Space — Sentinel-1/2 download auth.
# Currently the backend fetches S2 via Microsoft Planetary Computer
# (anonymous + SAS tokens), so these are NOT required. Fill in only
# if you add a CDSE-backed fetch path.
# CDSE_CLIENT_ID=
# CDSE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ECMWF CDS — ERA5 reanalysis. Not wired today; env_data.py uses
# Open-Meteo which is key-free.
# CDS_API_KEY=

# NREL → NLR solar resource data (domain migrates April 30 2026). Not
# wired today; analyze.py uses heuristics.
# NLR_API_KEY=
